The paper proposes a deep learning model for mobile and embedded devices, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The focus on reliability and uncertainty estimations suggests a potential fit for the sub-categories of multi-agent systems (cs.MA) and control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the use of dropout and predictive distribution estimation for inference operations suggests a potential fit for the sub-category of neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
